word_group.brief_definition: 胃部不适；胃难受；肚子难受

bilingual.source: I've got a stomach ache and my head hurts.
My stomach hurts because I haven't eaten since yesterday.
bilingual.target: 我的胃痛因为我从昨天起就没吃东西。

bilingual.source: They will also help your stomach get ready for the food you are about to eat.
bilingual.target: 它们还会帮助你的胃为即将吃的食物做好准备。

bilingual.source: On the day of the concert, I was so nervous that I woke up with butterflies in my stomach.
bilingual.target: 演出那天，我紧张得早上起来就觉得胃里翻腾。

bilingual.source: The gastroesophageal junction is where the esophagus meets the stomach.
bilingual.target: 胃食管连接处是食管与胃相接的地方。

bilingual.source: The oes connects the throat to the stomach.
Eating too much can bloat your stomach.
bilingual.target: 吃得太多会使你的胃膨胀。

list.abstract: stomach，英 [ˈstʌmək]，美 [ˈstʌmək]。英文单词，作名词时，指的是胃；食欲；胃口；肚子；腹部；倾向；四胃之一；类胃器官；欲望。作动词时，指的是能吃；消化；忍受；忍耐。短语搭配为“stomach ache（胃痛；胃疼；肚子疼）”。例句为“When your stomach feels full, stop eating.（当你的胃感到饱时，停止进食）”。 stomach近义词为abdomen，stand，suffer from。

yingyinNormal.en: Why do I have a sick feeling in my stomach?
yingyinNormal.zh: 为什么我感觉胃里一直犯恶心？

yingyinNormal.en: I'm not hungry. You lost a hand, not a stomach.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我不饿。你丢了一只手，又没丢了胃。

yingyinNormal.en: In my stomach. It's all warm. I always had a knot there, and now it's gone.
yingyinNormal.zh: 在我的胃里，暖暖的，我以前老是胃疼，现在不会了。

yingyinNormal.en: This will be the size of your new stomach. After gastric bypass surgery, portion control is critical.
yingyinNormal.zh: 之后你的胃大概就是这么大。胃旁路手术后，食量的控制至关重要。

yingyinNormal.en: You need to put something in your stomach, William. Toast, pills, juice. That's the order. Okay?
yingyinNormal.zh: 你得先吃点东西垫垫胃，威廉。吐司，药片和果汁，按这顺序来，好吗？

yingyinNormal.en: You walked me to the train station. But I felt a pain in my stomach. I thought it must have been something I ate.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你送我到火车站，而我突然胃里一阵绞痛，我还以为是我吃错了什么东西。

yingyinNormal.en: Since I don't have a brain they're coming from my stomach, down deep below and then up again into my mind.
yingyinNormal.zh: 因为我没有大脑，它们就从我的胃里钻出来，深深地下沉，再上升进入我的思想。

yingyinNormal.en: Ladies, please. These four walls once housed an intellectual salon where the mind received nourishment as well as the stomach.
yingyinNormal.zh: 女士们，自制啊。这间屋子曾是一个智慧的集合地，在这里，大脑和胃袋都能吸收到营养。

yingyinNormal.en: If you overeat or eat something that your new stomach can't tolerate, you may get violently ill, shakes, vomiting, sweats, diarrhea, fainting.
yingyinNormal.zh: 如果你进食过量或吃了你的胃无法消化的东西，会造成剧烈的不良反应，发抖，呕吐，汗流不止，腹泻，昏迷。

yingyinNormal.en: So, Brycie, how do you think he's gonna digest that? Stomach acid? You'd like to think that.
yingyinNormal.zh: 布莱斯 你觉得它要怎么消化？胃酸？就知道你会这么说。

yingyinNormal.en: Your body turns it into GHB on contact with stomach acid, but when you take it or when I sell it. It isn't GHB.
yingyinNormal.zh: 接触到胃酸后你的身体就会将它识别为G水，但在人买它或我卖它时它并不是G水。

yingyinNormal.en: The bullet to the thorax was the one that killed him. The other two shots, the one to the right shoulder and the stomach, they were survivable.
yingyinNormal.zh: 胸部的子弹是致命伤，其他两处枪击，即右肩和胃部的，都不是致命的。

yingyinNormal.en: How are you feeling? My stomach aches, I got the chills, my mouth tastes weird, it hurts to swallow, and I've got a little double vision. Yeah. I'm feeling better, too.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你感觉怎么样了？我胃疼，恶寒，嘴巴里的味道怪怪的，吞口水都疼，我看东西还有点重影。是的。我也好多了。

yingyinNormal.en: Lucy. What did you do to my stomach?
yingyinNormal.zh: 露西。你对我的肚子做了什么？

yingyinNormal.en: This is too much to handle on an empty stomach.
yingyinNormal.zh: 太难以置信了。

yingyinNormal.en: Beautiful, tall, sexy, showing her stomach? Look at all the boxes!
yingyinNormal.zh: 美丽、高挑、性感、露肚脐？你看这堆箱子。

yingyinNormal.en: I got a pit in my stomach the size of a sow's tit. Cook up that rabbit.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我肚皮上落了个疤，猪奶头那么大，兔子烤起来。

yingyinNormal.en: It made me ill, Francis. My stomach turned. Why, because you had to resign?
yingyinNormal.zh: 真让我恶心，弗兰西斯。为什么，因为你得辞职吗？

yingyinNormal.en: It took a steel goddamn stomach, and so has everything else we had to do since.
yingyinNormal.zh: 那需要莫大的勇气，自此之后我们不得不做的一切都是如此。

yingyinNormal.en: Now, if you wanna work with us on this bill, I can stomach a gun friendly candidate.
yingyinNormal.zh: 如果你愿意在法案上与我们合作，我就能容忍一个爱枪的候选人。

word_usage.usage:
stomach doing sth. 意为“忍受做某事”，常用于否定句和疑问句中，如：
He could not stomach working for the landlord night and day.
他不能忍受夜以继日地为房东工作。
